BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 15 May (MENA) -- Muhammad Ahmad Juwayd, a 
police driver from the al-Ghanayim District police force in the 
Asyut Governorate in Upper Egypt, was killed today when 
unidentified gunmen fired at him as he was driving to work. A 
responsible security source in the Interior Ministry said that 
the policeman succumbed to his wounds and the culprits managed 
to flee. Commanders from the Asyut Security Directorate, various 
investigation agencies, and experts of the criminology 
laboratory went to the scene to investigate. The Prosecution 
Office has been notified to begin investigations. 

